-- Petroplus Holdings Plants, UCB Names French Chief: European Equity Preview
-- B y   K s e n i a   G a l o u c h k o
-- 2011-12-29T05:00:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-28/petroplus-holdings-ucb-european-equity-preview.html
The following companies’ shares may
have unusual moves in  European (SXXP)  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses.  The  Stoxx Europe 600 Index  dropped 0.7 percent to 240.20.
The  Stoxx 50 Index (SX5P)  declined 0.6 percent to 2,329.47. The  Euro
Stoxx 50 Index (SX5E) , a benchmark measure for nations using the euro,
retreated 1.5 percent to 2,255.03.  Petroplus Holdings AG  (PPHN SW): The European refiner
fighting to secure crude supplies amid a $1 billion credit
freeze said it may have to start shutting plants if it can’t
come to an agreement with lenders. Petroplus declined 11 percent
to 1.65 francs.  UCB SA (UCB)  :  Belgium ’s biggest drugmaker named Michele
Antonelli as managing director of its French business and said
Chief Operating Officer Mark McDade will take over Antonelli’s
current mandate as head of technical operations. UCB rose 1.6
percent to 32.28 euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
